description: This is used by SaaS partners to write events to a customer's partner event bus. Amazon Web Services customers do not use this operation. For information on calculating event batch size, see Calculating EventBridge PutEvents event entry size in the EventBridge User Guide.

nested_items.name: FailedEntryCount
nested_items.description: The number of events from this operation that could not be written to the partner event bus.

nested_items.name: Entries
nested_items.description: The results for each event entry the partner submitted in this request. If the event was successfully submitted, the entry has the event ID in it. Otherwise, you can use the error code and error message to identify the problem with the entry.

nested_items.name: ErrorCode
nested_items.description: The error code that indicates why the event submission failed.

nested_items.name: ErrorMessage
nested_items.description: The error message that explains why the event submission failed.
